<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; " ><tr ><td align="left" valign="top" class="stack" style="color:#666666; font-size:14px; line-height:22px; padding-bottom:20px; " ><div class="mktEditable" id="business-update-entry" >
<p><span id="docs-internal-guid-e92b2559-6670-69b0-0eee-8c179a7ffddd"> </span></p>
<p class="normal"><span id="docs-internal-guid-4232d4fd-5da5-ca7b-b552-bdb47c5ddfff"><span>I&rsquo;m pleased to report that we closed out the first quarter of 2016 strongly.
    We were the bright spot in EMC&rsquo;s recent earnings call, growing revenues 56% year-on-year for Q1, with a market that has warmed to </span><a style="color: #059a91; text-decoration: none;" href="http://pivotal.io/platform"><span>Pivotal Cloud Foundry</span></a><span> and our </span><a style="color: #059a91; text-decoration: none;" 
href="http://pivotal.io/big-data/pivotal-big-data-suite"><span>Big Data Suite</span></a><span> software.
    We reported an impressive 200% year-on-year growth in annualized recurring revenue (ARR) on subscriptions, with a total ARR of $115 million.
    As noted in the past, growing annual subscription revenues helps create a more predictable business and is a key factor in achieving profitability.<br /><br /></span></span>Despite great year-on-year growth, our expenses were higher than expected, and we narrowly missed our ambitious ARR target in Q1.
    I ask that you continue to exercise discipline in how and where you spend&mdash;a key requirement to becoming a highly successful, independent company.
    &nbsp;<br /><br /><strong>Customers and Partners for the World<br /><br /></strong>The world&rsquo;s top companies are choosing to innovate and run their businesses on Pivotal products.
    This was underscored by one of the world&rsquo;s largest financial institutions signing a long-term strategic collaboration with Pivotal.
    We also mirrored a fourth quarter win with one of world&rsquo;s largest retailers when another Fortune 50 retailer chose Pivotal in Q1 as its strategic partner for digital transformation.</p>
<p class="normal"><br />We inked notable technical and go-to-market <a style="color: #059a91; text-decoration: none;" href="http://www.businessinsider.com/pivotal-on-the-cloud-wars-with-amazon-microsoft-and-google-2016-4">partnerships</a> with cloud providers Google,  Microsoft, and <a style="color: #059a91; text-decoration: none;" 
href="http://pivotal.io/platform/press-release/pivotal-teams-up-with-cisco">Cisco</a>, adding to our partnerships with AWS, VMware, and OpenStack.
   We now work with every major IaaS vendor and cloud provider.
   This flexibility has no parallel in the industry, and it evinces our case that <a style="color: #059a91; text-decoration: none;" href="http://pivotal.io/platform">Pivotal Cloud Foundry</a> is the world&rsquo;s most powerful continuous innovation cloud platform.
   As we expand our footprint and customer base across the automotive, financial services, insurance, retail and telecommunications industries, we are becoming synonymous with these big-name cloud leaders.<br /><br />Overall, the first quarter has put us on course for a solid mid-year report, so stay tuned!</p>
</div>
