<a href="#product-update" name="product-update"></a><table width="600" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" class="full-block" style="border-collapse:collapse; " ><tr ><td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" ><table cellpadding="40" cellspacing="0" border="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; " ><tr ><td align="left" valign="middle" class="text-block" style="padding-bottom:10px; color:#666666; font-size:13px; line-height:22px; " ><div class="mktEditable" id="product-update-title" style="padding-bottom:20px; " ><img style="display: block;" src="http://connect.pivotal.io/rs/625-IUJ-009/images/ncayou-portrait.png" alt="Nick" align="right"><img style="display: block;" src="http://connect.pivotal.io/rs/625-IUJ-009/images/jmckenty-portrait.png" alt="Josh" align="right"> <span style="color: #666666; font-size: 12px; line-height: 16px;">PRODUCT UPDATE</span><br> <span style="margin: 0; font-size: 20px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 24px; text-transform: uppercase;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-e92b2559-6671-674d-5341-68b630d91b08"><span><span id="docs-internal-guid-de0effd0-58d0-d520-b25f-23f1a6a794f1"><span>Pivotal and the New Global Ecosystem</span></span></span></span></span><br> <span style="color: #666666; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-de0effd0-58d0-a762-a38e-1049ae874600"><span>Nick Cayou, Vice President, Global Ecosystem, and Josh McKenty, Global Ecosystem Engineering</span></span></span></div>
<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; " ><tr ><td align="left" valign="top" class="stack" style="color:#666666; font-size:14px; line-height:22px; padding-bottom:20px; " ><div class="mktEditable" id="product-update-entry" >
<p>It&rsquo;s been a veritable <a style="color: #059a91; text-decoration: none;" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cambrian_explosion">Cambrian explosion</a> for those of us engaged in partner and ecosystem activities for Pivotal, with surging growth and diversification across our strategic technology partners, ISVs (independent software vendors), SI&rsquo;s (system integrators), and   
Federation partners within a very short timeframe.
   <br /><br /> This ecosystem of partners is key to helping Pivotal and its platform of continuous innovation remain at the center of the software-driven transformation across the enterprise.
   We formed the new <a style="color: #059a91; text-decoration: none;" href="https://sites.google.com/a/pivotal.io/inside-pivotal/corporate-marketing/corporate-communications/news-archive/global-ecosystem">Global Ecosystem Team</a> to cultivate and expand the mutual business and technology value created through them.<br /><br /> Here is summary of the biggest developments within this  
ecosystem:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>ISV&rsquo;s:</strong> Customers increasingly view our platform as central to their application, cloud, and cultural transformations.
   However, we can&rsquo;t do this alone.
   ISVs help us extend our value and are key to our growth.
   Josh McKenty spearheaded an immensely successful <a style="color: #059a91; text-decoration: none;" href="https://blog.pivotal.io/pivotal-cloud-foundry/news/industry-day-signals-big-things-for-cloud-foundry-ecosystem">ISV day</a> in February that lit the fuse with our ISV ecosystem partners.
   We&rsquo;re actively engaged in helping dozens of ISV partners integrate deeply with PCF, largely to serve the requirements of our largest customers.
 </li>
<li> <strong>Systems Integrators:</strong> Global and regional SI&rsquo;s are important to Pivotal in many ways.
   Most importantly, they help us scale our delivery and grow our PCF footprint in accounts.
   They bring application development services to larger enterprises who have scaling, geographic, or other requirements that we cannot serve through Labs.
   The <a style="color: #059a91; text-decoration: none;" href="https://blog.pivotal.io/pivotal-cloud-foundry/news/introducing-the-pivotal-ready-partner-program">Pivotal Ready Partner program</a> launched in May helps us formally onboard SI partners.
   To date, we have over a dozen signed partners, with many engaged in client accounts.
 </li>
<li> <strong>Strategic Partners:</strong> Larger systems vendors and public cloud providers have opened up new partner opportunities for Pivotal.
   In December, we <a style="color: #059a91; text-decoration: none;" href="http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20160216005696/en/Pivotal-Announces-Reseller-Agreement-Cisco-Deliver-Pivotal">announced</a> how our new partner, Cisco Systems, would resell Pivotal Cloud Foundry globally.
   In March, we completed the initial technical integration with Google Cloud Platform, and showcased this at <a style="color: #059a91; text-decoration: none;" href="https://cloudplatform.googleblog.com/2016/03/how-Google-is-bringing-cloud-computing-innovation-to-the-enterprise.html">Google NEXT</a>.
   We&rsquo;re working hand-in-hand with Google on select large accounts, and moving to broader product integration and joint marketing.
   In April, Pivotal and Microsoft announced the availability of PCF through the <a style="color: #059a91; text-decoration: none;" href="https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/marketplace/partners/pivotal/pivotal-cloud-foundryazure-pcf/">Azure Marketplace</a>, and Pivotal was <a style="color: #059a91; text-decoration: none;" href="https://channel9.msdn.com/Events/Build/2016/KEY02">featured</a> in a   
keynote at  Microsoft&rsquo;s Build conference in front of 5,000+ developers.
   We are pursuing over 100 opportunities jointly, and we expect to rev up our go-to-market efforts with Microsoft over the next few quarters.
 </li>
<li> <strong>Federation:</strong> We have expanded important partnerships with our federation partners, EMC, VMware, and Dell.
   EMC continues to embrace PCF, and will have more to announce on that at EMC World, while VMware and Pivotal announced a joint <a style="color: #059a91; text-decoration: none;" href="http://www.marketwired.com/press-release/pivotal-vmware-team-up-accelerate-deployment-cloud-native-applications-with-advanced-nyse-vmw-2118276.htm">PCF/Photon</a> play this week.
 </li>
</ul>
<p>Collectively, these are the most significant ties and the greatest influence we&rsquo;ve had in this ecosystem.
   We look forward to reporting back on our progress.</p>
</div>
